ror; assert generation completes, includes a `data unavailable` note in that section, and includes data from the remaining sections.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on model output fidelity, not only plumbing. Deterministic stubs would hide real failures in extraction, omission, or hallucination (LLM-DEP yes; deterministic-assertion trap applies). Single model decision step, so Workflow is not required unless multiple model decisions are chained. Rejection-gate: Integration rejected because behavior text explicitly requires \"accurately represents\" content quality of generated narrative.","test_description":"Use fixed input datasets with known key values, call the real summary model, and score outputs for factual inclusion/consistency of required values (e.g., exact numeric checks and contradiction checks), repeated across runs with pass-rate thresholds to account for non-determinism.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly spans real external boundaries (source APIs + email transport + inbox receipt), so real HTTP/email infrastructure is needed (REAL-INFRA yes; MOCK-HIDE yes). This is end-to-end system behavior; an in-process fake mailer could pass while real delivery/auth/routing fails. Rejection-gate: Agentic considered but rejected because the behavior text focuses on \"reaches ... inbox correctly\" (delivery path), not evaluating model output quality; Workflow rejected because no requirement for multiple agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Execute the script in a staging environment against real source endpoints (or staging equivalents) and real email delivery, then verify the configured mailbox actually receives the message with expected subject/body sections and recipient headers.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.72,"Agentic":0.13,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Core failure is orchestration/state persistence across runs: send failure -> local save -> next run retry. This can be reproduced with real modules plus a failing email adapter and real local filesystem in-process. System was considered due network/scheduler wording, but behavior can be validated without real SMTP outage or cron by invoking two runs and simulating unreachable send deterministically. Rejection-gate: System rejected because behavior text does not require validating OS scheduler or real provider outage semantics; Agentic/Workflow rejected because no AI output dependence.","test_description":"First run: configure email adapter stub to return unreachable error, run report generation, assert report file persisted locally. Second run: configure adapter to succeed, rerun scheduler entrypoint, assert persisted report is retried and file is cleared/marked sent.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.56,"System":0.32,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.03}}]}
